proof
set X = ( dom ( f1 + f2 ) );
X c= ( ( dom f1 ) /\ ( dom f2 ) ) by VFUNCT_1:def 1;
then A1: (X c= ( dom f1 ) & X c= ( dom f2 )) by XBOOLE_1:18;
A2: (( f1 | X ) is  continuous & ( f2 | X ) is  continuous);
now
let s1;
assume that
A3: ( rng s1 ) c= X
and
A4: s1 is  convergent
and
A5: ( lim s1 ) in X;
A6: (( f1 /* s1 ) is  convergent & ( f2 /* s1 ) is  convergent) by A1,A2,A3,A4,A5,CKB18:1;
then A7: ( ( f1 /* s1 ) + ( f2 /* s1 ) ) is  convergent by NORMSP_1:19;
A8: ( rng s1 ) c= ( ( dom f1 ) /\ ( dom f2 ) ) by A3,VFUNCT_1:def 1;
(( f1 /. ( lim s1 ) ) = ( lim ( f1 /* s1 ) ) & ( f2 /. ( lim s1 ) ) = ( lim ( f2 /* s1 ) )) by A1,A2,A3,A4,A5,CKB18:1;
then ( ( f1 + f2 ) /. ( lim s1 ) ) = ( ( lim ( f1 /* s1 ) ) + ( lim ( f2 /* s1 ) ) ) by A5,VFUNCT_1:def 1
.= ( lim ( ( f1 /* s1 ) + ( f2 /* s1 ) ) ) by A6,NORMSP_1:25
.= ( lim ( ( f1 + f2 ) /* s1 ) ) by A8,CKB2:1;
hence (( ( f1 + f2 ) /* s1 ) is  convergent & ( ( f1 + f2 ) /. ( lim s1 ) ) = ( lim ( ( f1 + f2 ) /* s1 ) )) by A8,A7,CKB2:1;
end;
then ( ( f1 + f2 ) | X ) is  continuous by CKB18:1;
hence thesis by RELAT_1:69;
end;
